<p>I am trying to scale all of the columns of a data frame, except for the first and last columns, and store the result in a new 'scaled' data frame.</p>  <p>Here is the code:</p>  <pre><code>df_rl_scl &lt;- df_rl for (jj in 2 : length(df_rl)-1) {          print (jj)     df_rl_scl[,jj] &lt;- scale(df_rl[,jj]) } </code></pre>  <p>The scaling is being applied to the first column in the data frame. When I added the <code>print(jj)</code> statement, the console shows that <code>jj</code> has values from 1 ... 40.</p>  <p><strong>Why does <code>jj</code>have a value of "1" the 1st time through the loop ?</strong></p>  <p>Console output of <code>print(jj)</code> statement :</p>  <pre><code>[1] 1 [1] 2 [1] 3 [1] 4 [1] 5 ...  [1] 37 [1] 38 [1] 39 [1] 40   </code></pre>